The Polk County Fair
The fair is hard work put in year-round by our intrepid volunteers and their families. The hard work put in is all worth it to see everyone enjoy it during those 4 days at the end of July. To see everyone enjoying the fair is the blue ribbon to top off all of our hard work.

show/polk-county-fair
Ticket Information
The Polk County Fair Society is a non-profit organization that promotes education for the youth in our community through the Polk County Fair. Many learning experiences and lifelong skills are learned through exhibiting at the fair. In 2019 there were more than 6,775 exhibitors. It is also an educational showcase of agriculture in our county. We pride ourselves in providing an opportunity for town and country to come together to celebrate our county. In 2023 our attendance was 44,000+ individuals.
